## Architecture Overview

**On-Device Layer**: Compact transformer (e.g., distilled BERT variant or MobileNet-style architecture) runs entirely on the user's device. This ensures no raw text transmission.

**Code-Switching Detector**: Lightweight model that identifies EN/ES transitions and language boundaries, routing each segment to the appropriate model variant.

**Per-Tenant Adapters**: Small adapter layers (e.g., LoRA-style) trained on tenant-specific data, injected between the encoder and classifier.

**Cloud Offload**: When encountering rare languages or ambiguous sentiment, the system can dispatch minimal embeddings (not raw text) to cloud models, maintaining privacy.

**Drift Detection**: Statistical monitoring of prediction distributions per tenant; triggers alerts when KL-divergence exceeds thresholds.

**Canary Rollout**: Gradual traffic shifting (1% → 5% → 25% → 100%) with automated rollback if error rates spike or drift metrics exceed limits.

